results.name: List of nodes generating two branches in the tree defined in sequence A129129.
comment: The odd numbers begin 1 3 5 7 9 11 ... therefore a(n) begins 2 3 5 6 7 ...
example: The array is a tree structure as described by A128628. If a node value has only one branch the value is twice that of its parent node. If it has two branches one is twice that of its parent node but the other is adjusted as indicated below:
(4) note the index of the LPF (index(3) = 2
(6) calculate the prime associated with the value in step five (prime(1) = 2)
(7) The parent node generating the odd number 135 is (2/3)*135 = 90.
therefore 90 is a member of A129128
